oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Loading produce on cart
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Martha Virginia Roark Lovell (1872-1959) with her husband, Pleasant Louis Lovell (1856-1932), working with peach men in the Friendship community. Baskets of peaches are in front of her. They are loading or unloading the wagon. Other men on the wagon are peach pickers.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Carts & wagons; Horses; Couples
